cs.CR, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.DS, cs.DB 

This paper deals with privacy challenges in machine learning services, specifically in the context of attribute inference attacks. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The paper also proposes a minimax optimization formulation and a practical algorithm, which falls under the category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper deals with preserving utility while protecting attributes, which is related to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). Finally, the paper uses real-world tasks, which could fall under cs.DB (Databases).
